==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Comrade
<hw>Com"rade</hw> <pr>(? ⟦or⟧ ?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp.
<ets>camarada</ets>, fr. L. <ets>camara</ets>, a chamber; hence, a
chamber-fellowship, and then a chamber-fellow: cf. F.
<ets>camarade</ets>. Cf. <er>Chamber</er>.]</ety> <def>A mate,
companion, or associate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And turned my flying <qex>comrades</qex> to the charge.</q>
<rj><qau>J. Baillie.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I abjure all roofs, and choose . . . ⟦br⟧
To be a <qex>comrade</qex> with the wolf and owl.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>comradely</ent>⟦br⟧
